    "created_at": "2016-04-03T11:03:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-03T11:03:23Z",
    "body": "@nicozimmermann94 I think I have probably misunderstood your issue, there is actually no way to remove the white flash when you do page navigations, because browser works by downloading and rendering page in the same time, so when navigation happens you will see the progress of previous page getting erased and the new page getting rendered, which is the white flash you saw.\n\nThe only workaround is to avoid page navigations in your app completely, with techniques like ajax, otherwise your app will just behave like normal browsers.\n"
  },
